result.name: Tai Hua Restaurant

reviews.text: A very busy place, not too expensive and food is fine. Service is quick, just don't expect polite service.

Rating based on comparison with restaurants available nearby:
(Overall: 2.75)
Food: 3
Decor: 3
Comfort: 2.5 (lunch hours)
Service: 2.5 
Price: 3
Sanitation: 2.5

Typical Restaurant you would find in any poorer district. The service is poor as well as the waiters attitude. Usually during lunch hours the local population of office workers would waddle in, cramming together to fill the vacancies. 
Expect nothing special of the food. Sometimes it can even be very underwhelming. I ordered a beef brisket rice set here once, I got a bowl of radish and 3 small pieces of brisket. It's fine here if you haven't high standards and simply just want to fill your stomach. In and out like a Cash-cow.

reasonable price, open 24 hour, variety choice of food, mainly serve for local people live nearly or work late, or want to have a bit at late night..... you can hv coffee, tea, beef noodle, Chinese bbq pork, chicken, or sandwiches, lunch set or dinner set .....
Great food and HK Tea at reasonable prices
It’s good

result.name: Sha Tin Fun City

reviews.text: Good modern shopping centre but still interesting when you not from around here as a tourist.
The large neon signs imply lots of fun, in fact, there's actually only a tiny arcade and several billiards clubs.
Serve the local community well. No mainland chinese spoiling the place.

It has a number of restaurants for Yum Cha and steaks.  Opposite the road locates a government-run swimming pool.  In day time, the most popular sector maybe the China Travel Service  at the ground level.
Got a great (cheap chinese) steak place there.
